 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-slz","title":"Config: CLI and environment variable precedence","description":"## Overview
Implement the precedence system where CLI flags override environment variables override config file settings.

## Background & Rationale
Users need predictable ways to override settings:
- CI/CD systems often use environment variables
- One-off commands use CLI flags
- Persistent preferences live in config file

The precedence must be clear and consistent.

## Technical Approach

### 1. Layered Config Resolution
```rust
// In core/config.rs
pub struct ResolvedConfig {
    pub providers: Vec<Provider>,
    pub format: OutputFormat,
    pub timeout: Duration,
    pub no_color: bool,
    pub verbose: bool,
    pub pretty: bool,
}

impl ResolvedConfig {
    /// Resolve final config from CLI args, env vars, and config file.
    pub fn resolve(cli: &Cli) -> Result<Self> {
        let config = Config::load()?;
        config.validate()?;

        Ok(Self {
            providers: Self::resolve_providers(cli, &config)?,
            format: Self::resolve_format(cli, &config)?,
            timeout: Self::resolve_timeout(cli, &config),
            no_color: Self::resolve_no_color(cli, &config),
            verbose: Self::resolve_verbose(cli, &config),
            pretty: Self::resolve_pretty(cli, &config),
        })
    }
}
```

### 2. Per-Setting Resolution Pattern
```rust
fn resolve_format(cli: &Cli, config: &Config) -> Result<OutputFormat> {
    // 1. CLI flag (highest priority)
    if let Some(format) = &cli.format {
        return OutputFormat::from_str(format);
    }

    // 2. Environment variable
    if let Ok(format) = env::var("CAUT_FORMAT") {
        return OutputFormat::from_str(&format);
    }

    // 3. Config file
    if let Some(format) = &config.defaults.format {
        return OutputFormat::from_str(format);
    }

    // 4. Built-in default
    Ok(OutputFormat::Human)
}

fn resolve_providers(cli: &Cli, config: &Config) -> Result<Vec<Provider>> {
    // CLI --provider flag
    if \!cli.providers.is_empty() {
        return cli.providers.iter()
            .map(|s| Provider::from_cli_name(s))
            .collect();
    }

    // CAUT_PROVIDERS env var (comma-separated)
    if let Ok(providers) = env::var("CAUT_PROVIDERS") {
        return providers.split(,)
            .map(|s| Provider::from_cli_name(s.trim()))
            .collect();
    }

    // Config file
    if let Some(providers) = &config.defaults.providers {
        return providers.iter()
            .map(|s| Provider::from_cli_name(s))
            .collect();
    }

    // Default: primary providers
    Ok(Provider::primary_providers().to_vec())
}
```

### 3. Environment Variables
Document and support these env vars:
- `CAUT_PROVIDERS`: Comma-separated provider list
- `CAUT_FORMAT`: Output format (human, json, md)
- `CAUT_TIMEOUT`: Default timeout in seconds
- `CAUT_NO_COLOR`: Disable colors (1, true, yes)
- `CAUT_VERBOSE`: Enable verbose output
- `CAUT_CONFIG`: Override config file path

### 4. Integration with CLI
```rust
// In cli/args.rs - add this to Cli struct
impl Cli {
    /// Get resolved configuration merging CLI, env, and config file.
    pub fn resolved_config(&self) -> Result<ResolvedConfig> {
        ResolvedConfig::resolve(self)
    }
}

// In main.rs or cli commands
async fn run(cli: Cli) -> Result<()> {
    let config = cli.resolved_config()?;
    // Use config.format, config.providers, etc.
}
```

