 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-swp","title":"[EPIC] Time-to-Limit Prediction","description":"## Overview

Time-to-Limit Prediction transforms raw usage percentages into **actionable intelligence**. Instead of showing "65% used," show "65% used • ~1h 45m until limit at current pace."

## Strategic Importance (Why P1)

This is the simplest high-value feature possible with excellent ROI:
- **Low complexity**: Simple math once history exists
- **High immediate value**: Users can plan their work around concrete timeframes  
- **Differentiating**: Few tools translate percentages into time

## User Value Proposition

**Current state**: "Claude: 65% used (resets in 2h 30m)" - User has to do mental math.

**Target state**:
```
Claude: 65% used
        ├─ Resets in: 2h 30m
        └─ At current pace: ~1h 45m until limit ⚠️
```

User immediately knows: "I'm going to hit my limit before it resets. I should slow down or switch providers."

## Technical Approach

1. **Velocity Calculation**: Track `Δ usage / Δ time` over recent window (e.g., last hour)
2. **Prediction Math**: `remaining_capacity / velocity = time_to_limit`
3. **Comparison**: If `time_to_limit < reset_time`, show warning
4. **Edge Cases**: Handle low/zero velocity (sustainable), insufficient history (show nothing)

```rust
fn predict_time_to_limit(current: f64, velocity: f64, reset_minutes: i32) -> Prediction {
    if velocity <= 0.0 {
        return Prediction::Sustainable; // Usage going down or stable
    }
    let remaining = 100.0 - current;
    let minutes_to_limit = (remaining / velocity) as i32;

    if minutes_to_limit > reset_minutes {
        Prediction::Sustainable // Will reset before hitting limit
    } else {
        Prediction::WillHitLimit { minutes: minutes_to_limit }
    }
}
```

## Display Integration

- Integrate directly into `caut usage` output
- Warning indicators when limit will be hit before reset
- Color coding: green (sustainable), yellow (close), red (will hit)
- Works in both human and robot output modes

## Success Criteria

- [ ] Velocity calculated from recent history (configurable window)
- [ ] Time-to-limit shown alongside usage percentage
- [ ] Clear warning when limit will be hit before reset
- [ ] Graceful handling of edge cases (no history, zero velocity, etc.)
- [ ] JSON output includes prediction data for automation

## Dependencies

- **REQUIRES**: Historical Usage Tracking (EPIC 1) - needs history for velocity calculation
- Minimum viable: needs at least 2 data points to calculate velocity
- Better accuracy: 10+ data points over an hour

## Considerations

- Velocity is inherently noisy - consider smoothing (moving average)
- Different providers may have different usage patterns
- Weekend vs weekday patterns may differ significantly
- Consider showing confidence level based on data quantity","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T18:11:08.989548041Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-18T18:11:08.989548041Z","compaction_level":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-swp","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-smv","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-18T19:21:34.289222086Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","metadata":"","thread_id":""}]}
